<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Sparrow</strong></span> writes of his infant daughter, Sylvia: &ldquo;You can&rsquo;t say, &lsquo;Oh, she&rsquo;s a great guru&rsquo; like my old new-age friends always said of their babies. She seems nothing like a guru, except for her hand motions, which are serious and expressive and weird. She seems like a <em>person</em>, a strong-willed person trying to use her body, as if she&rsquo;s just gotten a camera out of a pawnshop and is patiently getting it to work.&rdquo;</p><a href="/contributors/sparrow" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

